body:
11-Azidoundecyl dihydrogen phosphate was synthesized with a simple two-step reaction based on our previous work [bib15], and was used as the binding ligand. Alkyne-terminated PGMA was synthesized with a reversible addition-fragmentation chain transfer (RAFT) polymerization technique, as described in detail elsewhere [bib14]. Alkyne-PGMA with other molecular weights was made with the similar procedure but different reaction durations. As listed in [tbl1]
                        , alkyne-PGMA polymers with four different molecular weights (<i>M</i>

                           <i>n</i>
                        ) and low polydispersity index (PDI, 

                        ) were synthesized with the well-controlled RAFT technique.
